<paragraph blockId="8.[151,1437,418,1126]" pageId="8" pageNumber="37">
Ground color of body yellowish-green (
<figureCitation box="[645,729,526,550]" captionStart="FIGURES 74–77" captionStartId="9.[151,264,900,923]" captionTargetBox="[270,1316,198,869]" captionTargetId="figure-301@9.[260,1326,193,879]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="FIGURES 74–77. Empoasca (Empoasca) lijiangensis, 74, head and thorax, dorsal view; 75, face; 76, whole body, lateral view; 77, whole body, dorsal view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5280508" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5280508/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="37">Fig. 77</figureCitation>
). Crown with yellow patch on each side of coronal suture (
<figureCitation captionStart="FIGURES 74–77" captionStartId="9.[151,264,900,923]" captionTargetBox="[270,1316,198,869]" captionTargetId="figure-301@9.[260,1326,193,879]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="FIGURES 74–77. Empoasca (Empoasca) lijiangensis, 74, head and thorax, dorsal view; 75, face; 76, whole body, lateral view; 77, whole body, dorsal view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5280508" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5280508/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="37">Fig. 74</figureCitation>
). Eyes black. Pronotum with yellow irregular patches on anterior margin of pronotum and under eyes. Forewing and hindwing semitransparent. Abdomen yellowish-green. Legs light yellow to green (
<figureCitation box="[1123,1208,598,622]" captionStart="FIGURES 74–77" captionStartId="9.[151,264,900,923]" captionTargetBox="[270,1316,198,869]" captionTargetId="figure-301@9.[260,1326,193,879]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="FIGURES 74–77. Empoasca (Empoasca) lijiangensis, 74, head and thorax, dorsal view; 75, face; 76, whole body, lateral view; 77, whole body, dorsal view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5280508" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5280508/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="37">Fig. 76</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="8.[151,1437,418,1126]" pageId="8" pageNumber="37">
Ventral abdominal apodemes short, only reaching segment 3, parallel-sided (
<figureCitation box="[1070,1155,634,658]" captionStart="FIGURES 45–53" captionStartId="8.[151,263,1946,1969]" captionTargetBox="[237,1345,1175,1919]" captionTargetId="figure-411@8.[231,1356,1161,1933]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURES 45–53. Empoasca (Empoasca) lijiangensis, 45, male pygofer, lateral view; 46, pygofer appendage; 47, abdominal apodemes; 48, connective; 49, anal tube appendage; 50, aedeagus, ventral view; 51, aedeagus, lateral view; 52, paramere; 53, subgenital plate." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5280505" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5280505/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="37">Fig. 47</figureCitation>
). Pygofer in lateral view with posterior margin broadly rounded; 13–14 stout setae in group along posterior margin, few slim setae near stout setae group (
<figureCitation box="[301,387,706,730]" captionStart="FIGURES 45–53" captionStartId="8.[151,263,1946,1969]" captionTargetBox="[237,1345,1175,1919]" captionTargetId="figure-411@8.[231,1356,1161,1933]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURES 45–53. Empoasca (Empoasca) lijiangensis, 45, male pygofer, lateral view; 46, pygofer appendage; 47, abdominal apodemes; 48, connective; 49, anal tube appendage; 50, aedeagus, ventral view; 51, aedeagus, lateral view; 52, paramere; 53, subgenital plate." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5280505" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5280505/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="37">Fig. 45</figureCitation>
); pygofer appendage following posterior margin of pygofer, not extended beyond pygofer, broadly bifurcated with dorsal branch much longer than ventral branch (
<figureCitation box="[960,1045,742,766]" captionStart="FIGURES 45–53" captionStartId="8.[151,263,1946,1969]" captionTargetBox="[237,1345,1175,1919]" captionTargetId="figure-411@8.[231,1356,1161,1933]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURES 45–53. Empoasca (Empoasca) lijiangensis, 45, male pygofer, lateral view; 46, pygofer appendage; 47, abdominal apodemes; 48, connective; 49, anal tube appendage; 50, aedeagus, ventral view; 51, aedeagus, lateral view; 52, paramere; 53, subgenital plate." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5280505" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5280505/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="37">Fig. 46</figureCitation>
). Anal tube broad at base, tapering and slightly sinuate toward apex (
<figureCitation box="[530,615,778,802]" captionStart="FIGURES 45–53" captionStartId="8.[151,263,1946,1969]" captionTargetBox="[237,1345,1175,1919]" captionTargetId="figure-411@8.[231,1356,1161,1933]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURES 45–53. Empoasca (Empoasca) lijiangensis, 45, male pygofer, lateral view; 46, pygofer appendage; 47, abdominal apodemes; 48, connective; 49, anal tube appendage; 50, aedeagus, ventral view; 51, aedeagus, lateral view; 52, paramere; 53, subgenital plate." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5280505" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5280505/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="37">Fig. 49</figureCitation>
). Subgenital plate in lateral view, curved gradually caudodorsad apically, not expanded apically; with numerous macrosetae and fine setae somewhat irregularly arranged; dorsolateral margin group A with 5 long stout setae subbasally and group B with 18–19 short microsetae on apical half (
<figureCitation box="[1338,1423,850,874]" captionStart="FIGURES 45–53" captionStartId="8.[151,263,1946,1969]" captionTargetBox="[237,1345,1175,1919]" captionTargetId="figure-411@8.[231,1356,1161,1933]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURES 45–53. Empoasca (Empoasca) lijiangensis, 45, male pygofer, lateral view; 46, pygofer appendage; 47, abdominal apodemes; 48, connective; 49, anal tube appendage; 50, aedeagus, ventral view; 51, aedeagus, lateral view; 52, paramere; 53, subgenital plate." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5280505" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5280505/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="37">Fig. 53</figureCitation>
). Paramere with 5 teeth on dentifer, 4–5 setae subapically, apex nearly straight in lateral view, curved laterad in ventral view (
<figureCitation box="[265,349,922,946]" captionStart="FIGURES 45–53" captionStartId="8.[151,263,1946,1969]" captionTargetBox="[237,1345,1175,1919]" captionTargetId="figure-411@8.[231,1356,1161,1933]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURES 45–53. Empoasca (Empoasca) lijiangensis, 45, male pygofer, lateral view; 46, pygofer appendage; 47, abdominal apodemes; 48, connective; 49, anal tube appendage; 50, aedeagus, ventral view; 51, aedeagus, lateral view; 52, paramere; 53, subgenital plate." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5280505" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5280505/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="37">Fig. 52</figureCitation>
). Connective broader than long, posterior margin medially emarginate (
<figureCitation box="[1150,1234,922,946]" captionStart="FIGURES 45–53" captionStartId="8.[151,263,1946,1969]" captionTargetBox="[237,1345,1175,1919]" captionTargetId="figure-411@8.[231,1356,1161,1933]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURES 45–53. Empoasca (Empoasca) lijiangensis, 45, male pygofer, lateral view; 46, pygofer appendage; 47, abdominal apodemes; 48, connective; 49, anal tube appendage; 50, aedeagus, ventral view; 51, aedeagus, lateral view; 52, paramere; 53, subgenital plate." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5280505" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5280505/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="37">Fig. 48</figureCitation>
). Aedeagus in lateral view with preatrium long, aedeagal shaft curved dorsally, narrowing to apex (
<figureCitation box="[1062,1197,958,982]" captionStart="FIGURES 45–53" captionStartId="8.[151,263,1946,1969]" captionTargetBox="[237,1345,1175,1919]" captionTargetId="figure-411@8.[231,1356,1161,1933]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURES 45–53. Empoasca (Empoasca) lijiangensis, 45, male pygofer, lateral view; 46, pygofer appendage; 47, abdominal apodemes; 48, connective; 49, anal tube appendage; 50, aedeagus, ventral view; 51, aedeagus, lateral view; 52, paramere; 53, subgenital plate." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5280505" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5280505/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="37">Figs. 50, 51</figureCitation>
). Gonopore terminal.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="8" pageNumber="37" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="8.[151,1437,418,1126]" pageId="8" pageNumber="37">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,337,995,1019]" pageId="8" pageNumber="37">Etymology:</emphasis>
The species name is derived from the location “Lijiang” in 
<collectingRegion box="[1016,1208,994,1018]" country="China" name="Yunnan" pageId="8" pageNumber="37">Yunnan Province</collectingRegion>
where the new species was collected.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="8" pageNumber="37" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="8.[151,1437,418,1126]" pageId="8" pageNumber="37">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,323,1066,1091]" pageId="8" pageNumber="37">Diagnosis:</emphasis>
The new species is similar to 
<taxonomicName authority="Vilbaste, 1968" authorityName="Vilbaste" authorityYear="1968" box="[673,1053,1066,1091]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Empoasca" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="37" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="furcata">
<emphasis box="[673,878,1067,1091]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="37">Empoasca furcata</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Vilbaste" box="[886,1053,1066,1090]" firstAuthor="Vilbaste" pageId="8" pageNumber="37" refId="ref4151" refString="Vilbaste, J. (1968) Uber die Zikadenfauna des Primorje Gebietes. Tallinn: Valgus, 178 p. (In Russian)." type="book" year="1968">Vilbaste, 1968</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, but differs in having the pygofer appendage furcated apically in lateral view.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
